question:
List the name of students that have attended more than 7 events.
name of students means the full name; full name refers to first_name, last_name; attended more than 7 events refers to COUNT(link_to_event) > 7
query: SELECT T1.first_name, T1.last_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.member_id = T2.link_to_member GROUP BY T1.member_id, T1.first_name, T1.last_name HAVING COUNT(T2.link_to_event) > 7
